Paul Allan
fields.bio: Paul is a second year Computing Science student. Paul went to a small high-school in Port Coquitlam and chose SFU because of how close it was to his house compared to UBC. Initially a 2012 froshee, Paul took 2 1/2 years off school to work after the Fall 2013 term, returning to find things somewhat similar to how he left them, except with the CSSS having a new vending machine and the froshees looking different than how he remembered them. In the past, he has been the Secretary (now know as the Director of Archives and Director of Communications) and the Executive at Large twice.

In 2014/2015 he served as president of the CSSS and in 2015/2016 served as the Applied Science Representative on the SFSS Board of Directors. Now in his final eight months at SFU, he's working on small projects within the CSSS, helping mentor and share my experiences with new student organisers, and represent his student union while on the SFSS Council.

fields.name: Gareth Jung Hwan Moon
fields.bio:
Gary is actually a 5th year MBB student, but he's been hanging out with the CS kids since Day 1 of 1st year. He's most likely in the CS common room playing EU4, playing his 1000th run of Korea or Prussia. Otherwise he's playing hockey, playing the violin at mass, cramming a semester's worth of MBB material in one sitting, or sending cute animal pictures to his girlfriend.
"Almost has his life together, all-around solid guy" -8.5/10 Yelp review

It ended up being pretty true. David can now be found sitting in the common room too much, generally being loud and occasionally running down the halls.

David likes to think he's decently friendly, so feel free to bug him about pretty much anything.

fields.name: Brandon Sherwin
fields.bio:
Brandon was born a young man with a fully-grown beard standing at 6'4, 22lbs, 12% body fat. His favourite food is raw bear cub that he hunted with a spear. Within 3 weeks he had found a gathering of 50 disciples that was following his every word. and he personally authored 20 books.

It's all been downhill so far from and there and this is how he finds himself at SFU, at the bottom of the trough of his life so far.

His spirit animal is a snail and his hobbies are making peanut butter sculptures.

He enjoys collecting vinyl records, watching films (his favorites being Pink Floyd the Wall, This is England, and The Wind Rises), and pondering why people still buy Apple products.

fields.name: Ryan Ramautar Vansickle
fields.bio: Ryan is almost entirely sure he used to live in Toronto. He has abandoned haircuts and good taste in music in the hope that he will one day attain enlightenment. There has never been a human being less suited to computer science, but he's totally doing his best. Offerings of free food will usually summon him to the common room, where you are invited to remind him how much he resembles Jesus. Is full of useless knoweldge, all of which is fair-trade and gluten-free. Available in Rose Gold, Zesty Lemon Spice, and Perpetual Disappointment™.

fields.name: Eric Meng Gao
fields.bio: a man on the run. Hiding from enemy spies since 2015. Currently posing as a 3rd year Computer Science Major. Is often mistaken for a cloud. Can be seen in the common room practicing battle tactics and simulations.

She is very excited for what there is to come during her first year in university, so feel free to invite her to play a game or to an event!

A talented linguist, Argus speaks four languages (English, Cantonese, Mandarin and French) and is looking to learn Russian. fields.name: Ryan Vansickle

There has never been a human being less suited to computer science, but he's totally doing his best. Has been hungry since 2008, and is full of useless knowledge, all of which is fair-trade and gluten-free. Available in Rose Gold, Zesty Lemon Spice, and Perpetual Disappointment.

fields.name: Liam Wilson
fields.bio:
Legend has it that Liam first appeared in the unholy halls of SFU in the distant year of 2015. Now, against all odds, he has somehow managed to battle his way through the endless bureaucracy and anxiety of university life to reach his final semester. 

After surviving past terms with the CSSS as First Year Rep and Exec At Large, he now inexplicably finds himself serving as a CSSS Exec once again, only proving that he is a glutton for punishment.

He is often found in his natural habitat, the Discord, where he is always willing to help answer your questions, argue with you about politics, or talk endlessly about pop-punk music. However, do not approach if you see him in real life, for he fears human contact and will endlessly fight you on why C# is objectively the best programming language.
